HEADWORD: Bombshell
<hw>Bomb"shell`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
bomb. See <er>Bomb</er>, <pos>n.</pos></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>something or someone that stuns or amazes,
especially suddenly and unexpectedly; <as>as, the news of the
president's affair was a political <ex>bombshell</ex>; a blonde
<ex>bombshell</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>bombsight</ent>⟦br⟧
